Intave seems to ignore or incorrectly account for modified player attributes, especially movement speed and jump height.

We have a system of characters that differ in their characteristics (attributes). For some of them—those with speed and jump attributes—the _physics_ react particularly aggressively. 

**Expected behavior:**
Intave should fully respect active player attributes and adjust movement checks accordingly.

**Actual behavior:**
Players with valid attribute-based speed or jump changes trigger movement-related checks.

